# PRIVATE BY DEFAULT.
# Ignore everything, then allow ONLY the kit files that are meant to ship.
# Reason: a brand-new file is hidden automatically. You must DELIBERATELY add it
# below for it to ever reach the public repo. Safe by default, not safe-if-you-remember.
/*

# ── kit files that DO ship (the public shelf) ───────────────────────────────
!/.gitignore
!/AGENTS.md
!/ceo-interview.md
!/claude-settings.json
!/DESIGN.md
!/how-it-works.html
!/rig-map.html
!/INSTALL.md
!/install.sh
!/KEYS.md
!/OBSIDIAN-MIGRATION.md
!/README.md
!/statusline.py
!/VERSIONS.md
!/aios-intake.md
# Shipped DIRECTORIES are allow-listed too: open the dir, re-ignore its contents,
# then un-ignore ONLY the named files. A new file dropped in any of these stays
# hidden by default — so even a blanket `git add .` can't publish it by accident.
!/bin/
/bin/*
!/bin/boot
!/bin/capture
!/bin/instagram-station
!/bin/obsidian-to-gbrain
!/starter/
/starter/*
!/starter/welcome.md
!/.claude/
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/
/.claude/skills/*
!/.claude/skills/onboard/
!/.claude/skills/level-up/
# context/ + departments/ hold the USER's filled instance data. A cloner has NO leak
# hooks (hooks don't travel with a clone), so the .gitignore is their only guard:
# ship ONLY the scaffolding, ignore everything /onboard + /level-up fill in.
!/context/
/context/*
!/context/README.md
!/departments/
/departments/*
!/departments/README.md
!/departments/_template/
!/decisions/
/decisions/*
!/decisions/log.md

# Everything else — SOUL.md, claude-memory/, RESTORE.md, REBUILD-PACKAGE.md,
# obsidian-bridge-decision.md, *.bak, and anything new — stays on your machine only.
.gstack/
